| :--------------- | :--------------------------------------------------- |
| 300              | 4.34 × 10⁻³                                          |
| 400              | 1.64 × 10⁻⁴                                          |
| 450              | 4.51 × 10⁻⁵                                          |
| 500              | 1.45 × 10⁻⁵                                          |
| 550              | 5.38 × 10⁻⁶                                          |
| 600              | 2.25 × 10⁻⁶                                          |

Above 600°C, the equilibrium becomes highly unfavorable at atmospheric pressure, as described by the [Van 't Hoff equation](/Van_%27t_Hoff_equation). However, the catalyst requires a minimum temperature, around 400°C, to function effectively. This forces a compromise: operating temperatures are typically between 400°C and 500°C, accepting a moderate equilibrium yield to achieve a practical reaction rate.

